choices.text:
the idiots who!!!!!!

While I am aware of this "one man, one vote" system, and have no problem with it as far as it goes, I agree with Benny and Barry, the Knesset system allows only two parties of note to dominate. With seven seats, my relatives in Israel simply have no voice, other than those of the leaders - whom primarily report to Shas Mendel, the head of Aguda & yes, I mean the notorious and horrendous body as well. Sadly, I hardly even know their names, because we voters might be expressing our opinion in a few, but it is entirely ignored by the whole of Amona. And this is by no means particular. This is and always has been the situation. The head of Shas can, take on the whole of Knesset, and at best fail, if failing at all. My electorate seems to have found and have been using Isrsel's top political Tamarin; an ailing man who socks money out like crazy. Another lurks in Israel's corridors of power, it's Prime Minister himself, and again forcefully serves his will on us the electorate. Knesset, also has four main parties, and then bounces around in a fashion that makes Fox news standards noteworthy. That's what I was born to!
